### WHAT THEY WILL DO: ###

· Provide support and advice to ADI DCE on a wide range of quality and academic matters;

· Use extensive knowledge of NZQA policies and processes to inform quality practices;

· Oversee and support ARF and QA kaihautu;

· Liaise with WBL and support WBL move into provider rules;

· Oversee the development of Te Pūkenga policy framework;

· Oversee development of Te Pūkenga QMS in alignment with other frameworks;

· Participate in Te Pae Tawhiti Steering Co as required;

· Manage NZQF transition from subsidiaries to Te Pūkenga

· Maintain collaborative relationship with NZQA;

· Provide advice and support on quality matters to other workstreams.

· Effectively manage any uncertainty which will affect the achievement of organisational objectives.

### WHAT THEY WILL BE: ###

The Kaikōkiri - Director Quality is responsible for the leadership of their relevant work programme within the Academic Delivery and Innovation workstream. They will ensure their work programme deliverables are achieved on time, on budget and in a manner that both deliverable and process gives effect to Te Tiriti o Waitangi. The position reports to the Deputy Chief Executive Delivery and Academic and is part of Academic, Delivery and Innovation leadership team.

### WHAT THEY WILL HAVE: ###

· Significant executive or senior leadership experience

· Extensive experience within the vocation education sector, in particular leading Academic Quality

· Experience applying co-design and bi-cultural frameworks and both leadership as well as working practice that gives effect to Te Tiriti o Waitangi

· Experience in setting both strategic and operational work programmes, with a strong understanding of the vocational education sector

· Demonstrated expertise in delivery of projects and the associated disciplines of good project management, including financial/budget management

· Experience in building positive working relationships with a diverse range of stakeholders

· Excellent interpersonal skills and proven ability in developing relationships across a business

· Resilience skills and a highly collaborative mindset
